TY  - JOUR
AU  - Jehiel, Philippe
T1  - On Transparency in Organizations
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdu040
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 82
IS  - 2
SP  - 736
EP  - 761
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - When is it best for the Principal to commit to not disclosing all that he/she knows in moral hazard interactions? I show that whenever the Agent would choose the same action under complete information at several distinct states, then full transparency can generically be improved upon. This implies that full transparency is generically suboptimal whenever the dimension of the information held by the Principal exceeds the dimension of the Agent's action. In a simple class of problems, I make further progress on the best disclosure policy assuming the Principal can either disclose fully the state or remain silent.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdu040
ER  - 



